Undid revision 1001743991 by ([[User talk:Orhanghazi|talk]]) But your citation sources didn't provide any kind of information you submitted here. Before you revert the verified version to unstable version, put this on talk page. If you did a mistake on citation, then change the citation, don't remove the entire information that been verified.

Reverted edits by [[User:Orhanghazi|Orhanghazi]]. Make sure you read all the citation sources carefully before inputted here. Your edits may be classified as [[Vandalism on Wikipedia|vandalism]], and it is harming the [[Wikipedia:List of policies|Wikipedia policies]]. Any kind of [[Wikipedia:Assume bad faith|bad faith]] edits isn't welcomed on Wikipedia. Some of your [[Wikipedia:Verifiability|verified]] edits still preserved.

Correcting the information. The information about ''pembayang'' and ''maksud'' didn't appear in the citation sources. New citation source added regarding to this topic. In UNESCO inscribed data, it is known as ''sampiran'' and ''isi''.

Relocating the history information to the "History" section. Also removed about Peranakan, Kristang, and Chitty because this information isn't stated in the citation source. You can contribute to providing that information by citing sources that mentioned it.

Reverted edits by [[User:Orhanghazi|Orhanghazi]]. If you wish to add thus information regarding to ''pantun'' topic, you can give additional citation source next to  Inang, Zapin, or Joget. But it should be removed from this information because the citation source didn't provide anything about Inang, Zapin, or Joget. You can learn more about citating sources [[Wikipedia:Citing sources|here]]. And you can learn about [[Wikipedia:Policies and guidelines|the policies and guidelines on Wikipedia]]
